n Execution and planning lead for all events across ASEAN – ensure an overall events plan is maintained across all audiences. Develop a process to enable partners to run events on behalf of Sophos.  Ensure a schedule of relevant webinars is in place.  Ensure Sophos business goals are met or exceeded reviewing outcomes of all events.  Includes management of large industry trade shows as deemed relevant to support. Creation and delivery of an annual marketing plan including budget management and ROI reporting ensuring activity is on time and within budget Work effectively as part of the APAC Marketing team contributing to overall team success and suggesting improvements to maximise performance. Manage Sophos supplier relationships (for example, telemarketing, 3rd party event companies, print, design) to ensure project objectives are met with excellent value-for-money for Sophos.Desired Skills and Experience5+ years in technology or similar marketing roles Marketing business-to-business solutions  through indirect channels in a technology company Building relationships with partners/resellers Execution of marketing  campaigns using websites, email, newsletters, direct mail and presentations, events Creation of business marketing plans Using CRM or other marketing systems to track marketing activities and investments Managing eventsAbout this companySophosSophos delivers the best IT security and data protection for businesses. We produced our first encryption and antivirus products back in the 1980s. And today our products protect over 100,000 businesses and 100 million users, in more than 150 countries.
